Female : Smaller than male ( 15.1 mm .), antenna 1 and 2 shorter, propodus of gnathopod 1 wider than propodus of gnathopod 2 , propodus of gnathopod 1 and 2 smaller than in male, pereopod 3,4 similar to male, pereopod 5 similar to male but with some long setae on antero-inferior margin of basis. In female, compared to male, merus and carpus of pereopod 5–7 with more and longer setae, uropod 3 and telson are smaller than male and less setose. Oostegite 1 (of gnathopod 2 ) is illustrated (
Figs. 6–7
).
